Amen. How about some language keywords like &quot;readable&quot; and &quot;writeable&quot;?<p>public class Foo {
 public readable int canSeeeMeButCantChange;
 public writeable int cantReadMe;
 public int existingBehavior;
}<p>These are pretty simple changes to the compiler and verifier. You would make canSeeeMeButCantChange an invalid &quot;left hand&quot; variable in the compiler, and the verifier would have to check for any writes to the fields. cantReadMe would be an invalid right hand variable, and a similar check for the verifier. Any other public field behaves as normal.
